Republic American Corp told theSecurities and Exchange Commission it raised its stake inBuckeye Partners L.P. to 963,200 limited partnership units, or8.0 pct of the total, from 744,200 units, or 6.2 pct.    Republic, which is controlled by Cincinnati, Ohio,financier Carl Lindner and his American Financial Corp, said itbought 219,000 Buckeye units between May 14 and 22 at pricesranging from 22.49 to 23.02 dlrs each, or about 5.0 mln dlrstotal. Reuter&#3;